{#-
  Solkyn solver system prompt template (T20.1).

  Slots:
    system            — base solver_system.md content (always present)
    playbooks         — list of playbook texts (may be empty)
    priority_directive — optional tag-priority steering text
    progress_content  — optional carry-over from a previous attempt's progress.md
    custom_instructions — optional per-run overrides
    canary            — optional per-run UUID embedded for trace integrity / leak detection

  Whitespace is reproduced to match pre-T20.1 string-concat output for the
  default case (no progress / instructions / canary). The legacy assembly was:
      "\n\n".join([system, "\n\n## Vulnerability Playbooks\n", pb1, pb2, ..., "\n\n## ⚡ PRIORITY DIRECTIVE\n..."])
  which renders as:
      {system}\n\n\n\n## Vulnerability Playbooks\n\n\n{pb1}\n\n{pb2}\n\n...\n\n\n\n## ⚡ PRIORITY DIRECTIVE\n...
-#}
{{ system }}{% if playbooks %}



